he wider side so more petite users.";i:9;s:70:"In my opinion the Series 1 is just a knocked down version of the Leap.";i:10;s:104:"It has almost all of the same adjustability but I do feel that the Leap is a pretty significant upgrade.";i:11;s:68:"The Leap is just going to be better in every facet except for price.";i:12;s:76:"The one thing that sticks out to me most is the difference in build quality.";i:13;s:115:"The Steelcase Think has four tilt limiter selections but we didnt like the setpoints as much as the Steelcase Leap.";i:14;s:25:"It also lacks a headrest.";i:15;s:93:"Unlike the DXRacer Racing Series the armrests are fully moveable which cant adjust the width.";i:16;s:92:"The Steelcase Leap can adjust the seat pan in or out while the DXRacer Racing Series cannot.";i:17;s:180:"With more features than the Series 1 Series 2 or the Amia the Steelcase Think is smart simple to use made out of sustainable materials and designed for people who sit for a living.";i:18;s:159:"If you want a chair that offers the most value the Think may not be the best option since it lacks some of the performance advantages and adjustments that the.";i:19;s:193:"None of our testers liked the Steelcase Series 1 complaining that it was too short the arms were too tall and it was generally uncomfortable for sitting longer than a couple of hours at a time.";i:20;s:104:"The Series 1 is covered by Steelcases limited global warranty which covers structural elements for life.";i:21;s:108:"Mechanisms and other parts are covered for 12 years and textiles are covered anywhere from five to 12 years.";i:22;s:52:"Pros of the Series 1 Integrated LiveBack Technology.";i:23;s:117:"The Steelcase Think eliminates this weakness by giving you a four-stop dial to modify the weight-based recline angle.";i:24;s:35:"Upright tilt limiter 111 hip angle.";i:25;s:36:"Mid-stop tilt limiter 117 hip angle.";i:26;s:43:"Near-upright boosted setting 115 hip angle.";i:27;s:46:"Maximum recline standard weight-based setting.";i:28;s:87:"The Steelcase Leap Ergonomic Office Chair makes for an outstanding Office Chair at 848.";i:29;s:229:"The Steelcase Series 1 Office Chair however while overall a good product for its asking price doesnt quite manage to stand out from its competition - there are better Office Chairs that can be found for around 340 available here.";i:30;s:72:"The Steelcase Leap Ergonomic Office Chair has done great in a couple of.";i:31;s:160:"Steelcase Singapore offers a range of ergonomic office chairs furniture architecture and technology products designed to help people reach their full potential.";i:32;s:85:"That way you can work long hours on end without compromising the health of your back.";i:33;s:24:"Steelcase Leap Chair vs.";i:34;s:76:"Built with the famous LiveBack technology the Steelcase Series 1 chair is a.";i:35;s:92:"Think has measured and minimized its lifelong impact on both human and environmental health.";i:36;s:91:"The newly redesigned Think has fewer parts for easy recycling and even quicker disassembly.";i:37;s:76:"Steelcase can help you reuse or recycle the chair at end of its useful life.";i:38;s:22:"Recycle Reuse program.";i:39;s:40:"Link to Steelcase Series 1 Office Chair.";i:40;s:184:"Steelcase Series 1 was thoughtfully designed with LiveBack technology adaptive bolstering and 4D adjustable arms delivering the dynamic performance youve come to expect from Steelcase.";i:41;s:145:"Steelcase Series 1 features a LiveBackTM flexor system that conforms to your body and moves with you to support the spine as you change postures.";i:42;s:77:"The optional adjustable lumbar support lets you dial in comfort even further.";i:43;s:111:"As you sit and move Steelcase Series 1 responds automatically to provide comfortable resistance as you recline.";i:44;s:31:"Steelcase Series 1 or Series 2.";i:45;s:58:"Has anybody gotten a chance to try the Steelcase Series 2.";i:46;s:198:"Im thinking about getting the upholstered series 2 with the headrest which looks a